Cover crops such as vetch and clover are planted after a row crop
column3: and are left on the field over winter.  Usually they are plowed down the following spring.  Their productivity represents parts of two growing seasons in different calendar years.  Thus
column4: assignment to a calendar year is somewhat ambiguous.  Fescue in T5
column6:
is not plowed down.

In 2002 the cover crops were mistakenly plowed in before a biomass sample could be taken. So there is no cover crop biomass data available for 2002.
